## 5. Incomplete Reconciliation Framework

Although reconciliation processes are described in the Model Governance Guide, these processes are not consistently applied across all AML and OFAC systems. The focus appears to be primarily on Prime/PCS, with limited coverage of other critical systems such as sanctions screening platforms and payment processing channels.

This incomplete coverage limits the institution’s ability to demonstrate that all relevant data is captured and processed. DFS 504 requires that institutions ensure the completeness of data feeding monitoring and filtering systems. Without comprehensive reconciliation controls, there is a risk that certain data populations may be excluded or improperly processed.

**DFS 504.3 Alignment Gap:** Fails under **(c) Data Integrity**
**Sources:**   

