## 7. Insufficient Evidence of Data Completeness

The documentation does not provide sufficient evidence that all relevant data is captured within AML and OFAC systems. While controls are described, there is limited documentation demonstrating population-level completeness across all systems and data feeds.

This is a critical gap under DFS 504, which requires institutions to demonstrate that monitoring and filtering systems operate on complete datasets. Without such evidence, there is a risk that certain transactions or customers may not be subject to monitoring or screening.

**DFS 504.3 Alignment Gap:** Fails under **(a), (b), and (c)**
