The change management framework does not consistently require assessment of data lineage impacts when changes are made to systems, rules, or data flows. This creates a risk that changes could inadvertently disrupt data integrity.

DFS 504 requires that changes to monitoring and filtering systems be evaluated for their impact on data completeness and accuracy. Without this, there is a risk of introducing undetected data issues.

