The Data Governance Committee Charter establishes a governance structure but does not explicitly address DFS 504 requirements or data lineage oversight. This limits its effectiveness in addressing regulatory expectations.

DFS 504 requires active governance over data integrity. Without explicit alignment, governance bodies may not focus on the most critical risks.

