## 14. Vendor Data Lineage Not Fully Controlled

The documentation does not fully address data flows involving third-party systems. This includes limited visibility into how data is processed by vendors and how outputs are validated.

DFS 504 requires institutions to maintain accountability for all data used in compliance systems, including data processed by vendors. Without clear controls, vendor dependencies create risk.

**DFS 504.3 Alignment Gap:** Fails under **(b), (c), and (d)**
